        "CVE-2021-4104"
      ],
      "description": "It was discovered that Apache Log4j 1.2 was vulnerable to deserialization of\nuntrusted data if the configuration file was editable. An attacker could use\nthis vulnerability to cause a DoS or possibly execute arbitrary code.\n",
      "id": "USN-5223-1",
      "instructions": "In general, a standard system update will make all the necessary changes.\n",
